to talk about population growth. And so any
population where you have a positive r. And

00:00:39.239 --> 00:00:45.300
r stands for growth rate. If you ever have
a positive r, you're going to follow a curve

00:00:45.300 --> 00:00:49.839
that looks kind of like this. You'll first
of all have exponential growth. And then eventually

00:00:49.839 --> 00:00:54.109
you'll run out of space or food. There's going
to be competition. And eventually you're going

00:00:54.109 --> 00:00:59.010
to hit what's called logistic growth. And
so we call this the j shaped curve. The exponential.

