00:01:24.289 --> 00:01:29.399
in the population. r is the growth rate. Remember
if it's ever positive, and how do we calculate

00:01:29.399 --> 00:01:34.039
growth rate? It's basically the number of
people being born minus the number of people

00:01:34.039 --> 00:01:37.810
who die. If we ever have a positive one, then
we're going to get this curve. Now it's not

00:01:37.810 --> 00:01:42.500
always radical like this. Sometimes it's going
to be really gradual like this. Sometimes

00:01:42.500 --> 00:01:46.880
it's going to be incredibly quick. Depending
on what the r value is. And then the last

00:01:46.880 --> 00:01:53.880
thing is K. K stands for carrying, let's try
to spell that right, capacity. And so basically

00:01:54.719 --> 00:02:00.770
that means in an area for a certain population,
there's like a maximum amount that they can

00:02:00.770 --> 00:02:05.119
support. And so we call that the carrying
capacity. And that's where the limit is. It's

00:02:05.119 --> 00:02:09.399
eventually going to level out on that. And
so if I were to talk about, in the real world,

