00:02:36.920 --> 00:02:43.230
what N r and K are. Another thing that's important
is that you understand the way life exists.

00:02:43.230 --> 00:02:49.860
This is the story of life and death. It's
going to vary. And we really have three different

00:02:49.860 --> 00:02:54.920
types. So you happen to be a type 1 survivorship
curve. And what that means is think about

00:02:54.920 --> 00:03:00.319
all of the kids in your class or all the kids
who were born on the same day that you were.

00:03:00.319 --> 00:03:03.530
Basically most of you are going to survive
that first day. And most of you are going

00:03:03.530 --> 00:03:07.340
to survive. Now a few people will die right
away, but most of you are going to survive.

00:03:07.340 --> 00:03:10.930
You're going to make it through your teenage
years. And your middle ages. And eventually

00:03:10.930 --> 00:03:15.819
you're going to drop off. And all of you are
going to die in these last 10, 15, 20 years.

00:03:15.819 --> 00:03:20.400
That's because we're type 1. We're humans.
And we give a lot of, you can see this right

00:03:20.400 --> 00:03:24.780
here, parental care to our offspring. Now
if we look at a frog. Here's some frog eggs

00:03:24.780 --> 00:03:29.920
down here. They show what's called a type
3 survivorship curve. On day one, thousands

00:03:29.920 --> 00:03:33.970
of little frogs, almost all of them die. But
a few of them survive. And then they're going

00:03:33.970 --> 00:03:37.739
to level off. And then they're eventually
all going to die. Now we also have something

00:03:37.739 --> 00:03:41.489
in the middle. Type 2 we call that. Song birds
are an example of that. And so they're going

00:03:41.489 --> 00:03:46.310
to die off at a linear rate throughout their
whole life cycle. And so robins are an example

00:03:46.310 --> 00:03:50.439
of that. Robins on average live about a year.
But some live a few months and some live three

00:03:50.439 --> 00:03:54.030
years. But on average they're just going to
drop off until they're all dead. The ones,

00:03:54.030 --> 00:04:00.049
the cohort, the ones that are born on that
