00:04:25.560 --> 00:04:30.759
and exploit a niche as fast as they can. And
so these are things that normally live in

00:04:30.759 --> 00:04:36.440
an unstable environment. They have high fecundity.
What does that mean? Fecundity basically means

00:04:36.440 --> 00:04:40.440
that they can make a lot of babies really
really quickly. In general these things are

00:04:40.440 --> 00:04:44.310
small. They don't live that long. And their
offspring just kind of are spread to the ends

00:04:44.310 --> 00:04:47.910
of the earth. And so an example of this would
be a dandelion. They show up really early

00:04:47.910 --> 00:04:52.729
in the spring. They reproduce quickly. If
you've ever seen a dandelion when it goes

00:04:52.729 --> 00:04:57.139
to seed, those seeds are just spread out.
Given very little parental care. Bacteria,

00:04:57.139 --> 00:05:02.740
insects, diatoms, which are algae are a type
