00:05:23.030 --> 00:05:28.080
things are going to put their lives basically
around carrying capacity. They're in it for

00:05:28.080 --> 00:05:33.380
the long haul. They're in it for exponential
and then that logistic growth. They want to

00:05:33.380 --> 00:05:38.340
live a long time. Generally they live in a
more stable environment. They're larger as

00:05:38.340 --> 00:05:42.440
far as body size. They're going to live a
lot longer. There's a lot of parental care.

00:05:42.440 --> 00:05:48.110
So you as a human are going to be a K selected
species. If we look at plants. Compare this

00:05:48.110 --> 00:05:53.240
to the dandelion. A tree like this. Some trees
will live hundreds if not thousands of years.

00:05:53.240 --> 00:05:57.979
Whales are an example of K selected species.
But you don't necessarily have to be big.

00:05:57.979 --> 00:06:01.889
This is an arctic tern that lives decades.
